## 14. What are the most important lessons from this project?

These are the key ideas you should remember:

- correctness comes before optimization
- matrix multiplication is the main performance hotspot
- memory access patterns matter a lot
- caching reused transformed data can save repeated work
- multithreading helps when the workload is large enough
- performance must be measured, not guessed
- a good project is easier to explain when it has a clean presentation layer

